    "name": "Emanuela Gubinelli",
    "profile": "Emanuela Gubinelli (a.k.a Taleesa) was born on the 11/19/60 in Matelica (Macerata), and raised in Manhattan Beach, California, USA. She received a very strict education. She studied in a religious college and learned how to sing, play piano and violin. She started singing in a local band at the tender age of 9. Then, as she was still an adolescent, she escaped from home to follow her rock band for a tour in Europe.\r\n\r\nAfter this tour, the young Emanuela signed a contract with WEA, but it proved not to be exactly what she wanted. So after 2 years she broke the contract and moved to Milan, Italy, to give a new direction to her career. She started working in studio as composer and arranger.\r\n\r\nShe started gaining credibility as author when the 2 songs (Say Yeah and Keep On Jammin) she had written for [a=Stefano Secchi] became hits. This allowed her to restart her singer career and to record songs such as One Love the Lifetime, Living 2 Love and Baby Don't Stop that had some success in Fra",
